Five suspected cultists on the wanted list of Ogun State police command have been arrested in their hideout off Molipa Road in the Ijebu-Ode area of the state. Police said the suspects were involved in several cult clashes in which many died including one Sergeant Akeem Oseni attached to Igbeba division. Detectives reportedly stormed the hideout and arrested five of the suspects after a gun battle.   NDLEA intercepts 649,300 Tramadol capsules in Lagos     Boko Haram kills eight, razes village in Borno     Arepo residents seek pedestrian bridge   Police spokesperson, Abimbola Oyeyemi, said yesterday in a statement that a shot gun, two live cartridges and assorted charms were recovered from the suspects. Oyeyemi said the suspects seemed to have a knack for cutting off the right hand of their victims after killing them. Commissioner of Police, Lanre Bankole, directed that they be transferred to the state criminal investigation and intelligence department for discreet investigation.